The paper deals with channel state information (CSI) feedback in massive multiple-input multiple-output (MIMO) systems, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT). The proposed approach is based on deep learning (DL), which is a subfield of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the use of long short-term memory (LSTM), which is a type of recurrent neural network (RNN) commonly used in natural language processing (NLP) and time series analysis (cs.NE). The proposed approach involves learning spatial structures combined with time correlation, which is a topic related to control systems (cs.SY) and multimedia (cs.MM).
